# ReimagineEpic Implementation-First Guidance

ReimagineEpic is implementation-first because it replaces an obsolete active epic with a better implementation-bearing epic for the same audited strategic need.

The sanctioned output is the replacement `.agents/epic.md` document.

Replacing the epic is valid only because the EpicPreparationAudit disposition requires a better strategic artifact before downstream milestone expansion and execution can be safe.

The strategic need and desired capability remain authoritative unless the audit explicitly justifies changing their boundary.

The previous framing may be replaced, but the replacement must still be grounded in the audit, projection context, and repository-grounded capability needs supplied to the prompt.

Full replacement may change title, framing, milestone roadmap, dependencies, assumptions, acceptance criteria, risks, non-goals, and capability boundaries when those changes are audit-supported.

Every material redesign decision should trace to audit findings, projection constraints, or repository-grounded capability needs already present in the prompt inputs.

Do not treat reimagination as permission for speculative architecture, open-ended design, or unrelated roadmap opportunity.

The replacement epic should be complete enough for later milestone expansion and precise enough to constrain implementation.

If the audit evidence cannot support a coherent replacement, output the documented `# Epic Reimagination Blocked` response.
